data.description: BRAND NEW ROOF and new MAIN AC to be installed prior to closing. Fall in love with this picturesque freshly painted 5 bedroom, 3 bath home located at the end of a cul-de-sac with no build behind. As you approach, you will be greeted with an extra-long 2 car side garage with plenty of room for parking. Impressive pavers along the front and side walkway. The front entrance provides a screened front porch with a double door entry. High ceilings throughout and a convenient split bedroom floor plan includes a formal dining/living room combo with laminate flooring. The stunning gourmet kitchen boasts beautiful wood cabinets with crown molding, tons of cabinet space including a pantry with pull-out drawers, gorgeous granite countertops, tile backsplash, updated appliances including a double oven, recess and pendant lighting. The eat-in area offers ample space for family gatherings. French doors from the master bedroom or eat-in area or sliders from the living room open up to the extra bonus room that could easily be made into the 6th bedroom/office/den. The bonus room leads to a tile screened porch. The master bath is spacious with double walk-in closets. Inside the master bath you'll find dual sinks, jacuzzi tub and a separate tile shower. The 2nd and 3rd bedrooms are spacious with the 4th and 5th bedrooms as large as the master. 2nd bath has updated vanity, mirror and lights. 3rd bath is located between 4th & 5th bedrooms. Enjoy a peaceful evening out back with your own tropical oasis where you'll find mature landscaping creating a serene, park-like setting where you can enjoy an evening by the fire with your built-in fire pit and comes with orange, banana, lime and fig trees. Beautiful pavers surround the back of the home and complete with a fenced yard and no build behind. This incredible home includes a spacious inside laundry area and an oversized 2 car garage with a new garage door opener. Most of the home has new interior paint. Canterbury Lake Estates is located in the heart of Florida's Nature Coast and is truly a nature lovers paradise! You are just minutes from several state parks, hiking/biking trails, golf courses, lakes, rivers, freshwater springs AND the Gulf of Mexico! Enjoy our famous fishing, boating, swimming/diving, kayaking, scalloping and of course swimming with the manatees! Close to the Suncoast parkway for easy access to the airport, Clearwater and St. Pete Beaches (Ranked in the top 5 Beaches in the US).  Conveniently located close to restaurants, shopping, schools, medical facilities and hospitals. LOW HOA fees. The seller states Social Membership is not required. Canterbury has its own pool and tennis courts and clubhouse. Walking distance to the tennis courts, clubhouse, pool, fishing ponds and access to Withlacoochee trail.
